<p>Let'say i want to create some product pages on wordpress.</p>  <p>Eg: </p>  <p>example.com/product1 example.com/product2 example.com/product3</p>  <p>Now how can i add exact subpages to all of the pages?</p>  <p>Eg:</p>  <p>example.com/product1/intro example.com/product2/intro</p>  <p>example.com/product1/docs example.com/product2/docs</p>  <p>This is exact what roots.io does with it's pages (eg: <a href="https://roots.io/bedrock/intro/" rel="nofollow">https://roots.io/bedrock/intro/</a> ; <a href="https://roots.io/sage/intro/" rel="nofollow">https://roots.io/sage/intro/</a>)</p>  <p>The problem is i didn't found any solution for this aproach (using same subpages slugs for multiple parent pages).</p>  <p>How do they do it?</p>